LAD rewiring data: Cobl PAS integration in F1ES cells.

Bas van Steensel, Nov2018 - April2019.

Introduction

This script runs the Cast genome control analysis complementary to the 129 analysis of LAD_Rewiring__PASins_Cobl1_129genome_BvS190423.Rhtml

Description of Data

  • Simple read counts per GATC fragment.

Path, Libraries, Parameters and Functions

#directory:
setwd("~/mydata/Projects/LADrewiring/")

#general stuff:
StartTime<-Sys.time() #used to determine runtime, see very end of this doc
Date<-substr(gsub("-", "", Sys.time()),3,8)

#libraries:
library(GenomicRanges)
library(data.table) #for fast reading of data files
library(Sushi) #for plotting gene annotations

#parameters:
SMTH<-301 #smoothing window size (GATC fragments)

mygenes<-c("Cobl") #gene that is the center of the plots; may be multiple

set.seed(42) #for reproducible random sampling

Refseq gene annotations from UCSC

#gene coordinates:
gchrom<-c(); gstart<-c(); gstop<-c()
for(g in mygenes)
{wh<-which(Refseq.mm10$gene==g)
 gchrom[g]<-as.character(unique(Refseq.mm10$chrom[wh]))
 gstart[g]<-min(c(Refseq.mm10$start[wh],Refseq.mm10$stop[wh]))
 gstop[g]<-max(c(Refseq.mm10$start[wh],Refseq.mm10$stop[wh]))
}
gchrom<-as.character(gchrom)
print(data.frame(gene=g, chrom=gchrom, start=gstart, end=gstop))

#set extreme values of individual GATC fragments to the genome-wide mean:
mcols(DamID.Control)$Dam[mcols(DamID.Control)$Dam > 100*mean(mcols(DamID.Control)$Dam)] <- mean(mcols(DamID.Control)$Dam)
mcols(DamID.Control)$DamLam[mcols(DamID.Control)$DamLam > 100*mean(mcols(DamID.Control)$DamLam)]<-mean(mcols(DamID.Control)$DamLam)
mcols(DamID.Exp)$Dam[mcols(DamID.Exp)$Dam > 100*mean(mcols(DamID.Exp)$Dam)] <- mean(mcols(DamID.Exp)$Dam)
mcols(DamID.Exp)$DamLam[mcols(DamID.Exp)$DamLam > 100*mean(mcols(DamID.Exp)$DamLam)]<-mean(mcols(DamID.Exp)$DamLam)

#smooth:
sDamID.Control<-smooth.DamID(DamID.Control, ws=SMTH, pseud=30) #slightly higher pseudocount because of data sparsity
sDamID.Exp<-smooth.DamID(DamID.Exp, ws=SMTH, pseud=30)

Inspect data

How noisy are the data? Do they correlate well overall? Looks OK?

#scatter plot of Control vs Exp data:
notna<-!(is.na(mcols(sDamID.Exp)$logratio) | is.na(mcols(sDamID.Control)$logratio))
s<-sample(which(notna), 50000)
par(mfrow=c(1,1))
plot(mcols(sDamID.Control)$logratio[s], mcols(sDamID.Exp)$logratio[s], pch=19, cex=0.5, col="#00000022")
#highlight Exp gene:
COL<-rainbow(length(mygenes)) #plotting colors
for(g in 1:length(mygenes))
{w<-which(seqnames(sDamID.Exp)==gchrom[g] & start(sDamID.Exp)>=gstart[g] & end(sDamID.Exp)<=gstop[g])
 points(mcols(sDamID.Control)$logratio[w], mcols(sDamID.Exp)$logratio[w], pch=19, cex=0.5, col=COL[g])
 legend("topleft", pch=19, legend=mygenes, col=COL)
}
#correlation coefficients:
#pearson:
print(cor(mcols(sDamID.Control)$logratio, mcols(sDamID.Exp)$logratio, use="p", method="p"))

## [1] 0.9600234

#spearman:
print(cor(mcols(sDamID.Control)$logratio, mcols(sDamID.Exp)$logratio, use="p", method="s"))

## [1] 0.9543277

#is slope close to 1:
LM<-lm(mcols(sDamID.Exp)$logratio ~ mcols(sDamID.Control)$logratio)
print(LM)

## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = mcols(sDamID.Exp)$logratio ~ mcols(sDamID.Control)$logratio)
## 
## Coefficients:
##                    (Intercept)  mcols(sDamID.Control)$logratio  
##                     -0.0002838                       0.8301852

abline(LM, lwd=3, col="green")
abline(a=0, b=1, col="black", lty="dashed", lwd=3)
legend("bottomright", legend=c("diagonal", "linear fit"), col=c("black", "green"), lwd=3, lty=c("solid", "dashed"))


#use loess smoothing to straighten out banana-shapes etc:
#the reasonable assumption here is that most of the genome will remain unaffected, or at least will not show effects in the same direction.
#ord<-order(mcols(sDamID.Control)$logratio[s])
LOESS50<-loess(mcols(sDamID.Exp)$logratio[s]-mcols(sDamID.Control)$logratio[s] ~ mcols(sDamID.Control)$logratio[s], span=0.5)
#apply correction to experimental data:
mcols(sDamID.Exp)$logratio <- mcols(sDamID.Exp)$logratio - predict(LOESS50, mcols(sDamID.Control)$logratio)
#plot again: 
plot(mcols(sDamID.Control)$logratio[s], mcols(sDamID.Exp)$logratio[s], pch=19, cex=0.5, col="#00000022")
for(g in 1:length(mygenes))
{w<-which(seqnames(sDamID.Exp)==gchrom[g] & start(sDamID.Exp)>=gstart[g] & end(sDamID.Exp)<=gstop[g])
 points(mcols(sDamID.Control)$logratio[w], mcols(sDamID.Exp)$logratio[w], pch=19, cex=0.5, col=COL[g])
 legend("topleft", pch=19, legend=mygenes, col=COL)
}
LMcor<-lm(mcols(sDamID.Exp)$logratio[s] ~ mcols(sDamID.Control)$logratio[s])
abline(LMcor, lwd=3, col="green")
abline(a=0, b=1, col="black", lty="dashed", lwd=3)
legend("bottomright", legend=c("diagonal", "linear fit"), col=c("black", "green"), lwd=3, lty=c("solid", "dashed"))

Calculate domainograms

#calculate empirical domainograms:
w<-round(67*1.15^c(0:27)) %/%2 *2 +1 #odd windowsizes, exponentially increasing from ~40kb to ~2Mb
DG.Exp<-emp.domainogram(damid.exp=DamID.Exp, damid.ctl=DamID.Control, chrom=gchrom[1], window.sizes=w, up=FALSE, logratios=TRUE, loess.corr=LOESS50)
